# Kimchi workflow (required)

Full details: `AGENTS.md` in repo root.

## Branch discipline — never violate

- **Do not push to `dev` or `main`** unless San explicitly says "go ahead" for that push.
- **Always work on `feat/<name>`** branched from `dev`. One feature per branch.
- **Only `dev` and `main` deploy.** `feat/*` is GitHub-only until merged via PR.
- Flow: `feat → PR → dev → test on dev URL → San approves → main`.

## Where to test

- **Non-AI features:** browser-test on `https://kimchi-git-dev-second-ladder.vercel.app`
- **AI features:** UI on dev only; say clearly that AI E2E needs prod or San's manual test (no `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` on dev).
- **Passcode:** production (`kimchi.so`) only — dev staging has no passcode gate.

## Do not edit without approval

- `src/app/(workspace)/layout.tsx`
- `prisma/schema.prisma` (unless the task is explicitly schema work)

## Done means

Verified on dev in a browser when possible. Never report a feature complete from code alone.
